name: Ambush Commander
text: Forests you control are 1/1 green Elf creatures that are still lands.\n{1}{G}, Sacrifice an Elf: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Allosaurus Rider
text: You may exile two green cards from your hand rather than pay Allosaurus Rider's mana cost.\nAllosaurus Rider's power and toughness are each equal to 1 plus the number of lands you control.

name: Elvish Eulogist
text: Sacrifice Elvish Eulogist: You gain 1 life for each Elf card in your graveyard.
flavor: "No matter how adept our artistic skill, our effigies can never hope to capture the vibrant beauty of a living elf. Perhaps that is truly why we mourn."

name: Elvish Harbinger
text: When Elvish Harbinger enters the battlefield, you may search your library for an Elf card, reveal it, then shuffle your library and put that card on top of it.\n{T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.

name: Elvish Warrior
flavor: "My tales of war are the stories most asked for around the fires at night, but they're the ones I care least to tell."

name: Gempalm Strider
text: Cycling {2}{G}{G} ({2}{G}{G}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Gempalm Strider, Elf creatures get +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Heedless One
text: Trample\nHeedless One's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Elves on the battlefield.
flavor: "Channel your vitality through me."

name: Imperious Perfect
text: Other Elf creatures you control get +1/+1.\n{G}, {T}: Put a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: In a culture of beauty, the most beautiful are worshipped as gods.

name: Llanowar Elves
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: One bone broken for every twig snapped underfoot.\n—Llanowar penalty for trespassing

name: Lys Alana Huntmaster
text: Whenever you cast an Elf spell, you may put a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: From the highest tiers of Dawn's Light Palace to the deepest shade of Wren's Run, the silver notes of the horn shimmer through the air, and all who hear it feel its pull.

name: Stonewood Invoker
text: {7}{G}: Stonewood Invoker gets +5/+5 until end of turn.
flavor: The Mirari pulses in his veins.

name: Sylvan Messenger
text: Trample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)\nWhen Sylvan Messenger enters the battlefield, reveal the top four cards of your library. Put all Elf cards revealed this way into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Timberwatch Elf
text: {T}: Target creature gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is the number of Elves on the battlefield.
flavor: Even through the Mirari's voice, the elves still hear the call of their kinship.

name: Voice of the Woods
text: Tap five untapped Elves you control: Put a 7/7 green Elemental creature token with trample onto the battlefield.
flavor: The ritual of making draws upon the elves' memories and pasts. And elves have long memories and ancient pasts.

name: Wellwisher
text: {T}: You gain 1 life for each Elf on the battlefield.
flavor: "Close your ears to the voice of greed, and you can turn a gift for one into a gift for many."

name: Wirewood Herald
text: When Wirewood Herald dies, you may search your library for an Elf card, reveal that card, put it into your hand, then shuffle your library.
flavor: The goblins laughed as the elf ran away, until more came back.

name: Wirewood Symbiote
text: Return an Elf you control to its owner's hand: Untap target creature. Activate this ability only once each turn.
flavor: It drinks fatigue.

name: Wood Elves
text: When Wood Elves enters the battlefield, search your library for a Forest card and put that card onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Every branch a crossroads, every vine a swift steed.

name: Wren's Run Vanquisher
text: As an additional cost to cast Wren's Run Vanquisher, reveal an Elf card from your hand or pay {3}.\nDeathtouch (Any amount of damage this deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)

name: Elvish Promenade
text: Put a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token onto the battlefield for each Elf you control.
flavor: The faultless and immaculate castes form the lower tiers of elvish society, with the exquisite caste above them. At the pinnacle is the perfect, a consummate blend of aristocrat and predator.

name: Giant Growth
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Harmonize
text: Draw three cards.
flavor: "Life's greatest lessons don't come from focus or concentration. They come from breathing and simply noticing."\n—Seton, centaur druid

name: Wildsize
text: Target creature gets +2/+2 and gains trample until end of turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Two times the size, four times the smell.

name: Moonglove Extract
text: Sacrifice Moonglove Extract: Moonglove Extract deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Diluted, moonglove can etch living tissue. Concentrated, a drop will kill a giant.

name: Slate of Ancestry
text: {4}, {T}, Discard your hand: Draw a card for each creature you control.
flavor: The pattern of life can be studied like a book, if you know how to read it.

name: Tranquil Thicket
text: Tranquil Thicket enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\nCycling {G} ({G}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Wirewood Lodge
text: {T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.\n{G}, {T}: Untap target Elf.

name: Siege-Gang Commander
text: When Siege-Gang Commander enters the battlefield, put three 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens onto the battlefield.\n{1}{R}, Sacrifice a Goblin: Siege-Gang Commander deals 2 damage to target creature or player.

name: Akki Coalflinger
text: First strike\n{R}, {T}: Attacking creatures gain first strike until end of turn.
flavor: No matter where you find them, goblins love rocks.

name: Clickslither
text: Haste\nSacrifice a Goblin: Clickslither gets +2/+2 and gains trample until end of turn.
flavor: The least popular goblins get the outer caves.

name: Emberwilde Augur
text: Sacrifice Emberwilde Augur: Emberwilde Augur deals 3 damage to target player. Activate this ability only during your upkeep.
flavor: Legends say a djinn gave the goblins a gift they could never hope to master.

name: Flamewave Invoker
text: {7}{R}: Flamewave Invoker deals 5 damage to target player.
flavor: Inside even the humblest goblin lurks the potential for far greater things—and far worse.

name: Gempalm Incinerator
text: Cycling {1}{R} ({1}{R}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)\nWhen you cycle Gempalm Incinerator, you may have it deal X damage to target creature, where X is the number of Goblins on the battlefield.

name: Goblin Cohort
text: Goblin Cohort can't attack unless you've cast a creature spell this turn.
flavor: Akki shells provided good protection when downhill charging became headlong tumbling.

name: Goblin Matron
text: When Goblin Matron enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a Goblin card, reveal that card, and put it into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.
flavor: There's always room for one more.

name: Goblin Ringleader
text: Haste\nWhen Goblin Ringleader enters the battlefield, reveal the top four cards of your library. Put all Goblin cards revealed this way into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Goblin Sledder
text: Sacrifice a Goblin: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "Let's play ‘sled.' Here's how it works: you're the sled."

name: Goblin Warchief
text: Goblin spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.\nGoblin creatures you control have haste.
flavor: They poured from the Skirk Ridge like lava, burning and devouring everything in their path.

name: Ib Halfheart, Goblin Tactician
text: Whenever another Goblin you control becomes blocked, sacrifice it. If you do, it deals 4 damage to each creature blocking it.\nSacrifice two Mountains: Put two 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: "Everybody but me—CHARGE!"

name: Mogg Fanatic
text: Sacrifice Mogg Fanatic: Mogg Fanatic deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "I got it! I got it! I—"

name: Mogg War Marshal
text: Echo {1}{R} (At the beginning of your upkeep, if this came under your control since the beginning of your last upkeep, sacrifice it unless you pay its echo cost.)\nWhen Mogg War Marshal enters the battlefield or dies, put a 1/1 red Goblin creature token onto the battlefield.

name: Mudbutton Torchrunner
text: When Mudbutton Torchrunner dies, it deals 3 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: The oil sloshes against his skull as he nears his destination: the Frogtosser Games and the lighting of the Flaming Boggart.

name: Raging Goblin
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: He raged at the world, at his family, at his life. But mostly he just raged.

name: Reckless One
text: Haste\nReckless One's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Goblins on the battlefield.
flavor: "Release chaos with me!"

name: Skirk Drill Sergeant
text: Whenever Skirk Drill Sergeant or another Goblin dies, you may pay {2}{R}. If you do, reveal the top card of your library. If it's a Goblin permanent card, put it onto the battlefield. Otherwise, put it into your graveyard.
flavor: "I order you to volunteer."

name: Skirk Fire Marshal
text: Protection from red\nTap five untapped Goblins you control: Skirk Fire Marshal deals 10 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: He's boss because he's smart enough to get out of the way.

name: Skirk Prospector
text: Sacrifice a Goblin: Add {R} to your mana pool.
flavor: "I like goblins. They make funny little popping sounds when they die."\n—Braids, dementia summoner

name: Skirk Shaman
text: Skirk Shaman can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or red creatures.
flavor: In a shaman's grimy hands, a concoction of dried Skirk Ridge herbs can become the face of panic.

name: Tar Pitcher
text: {T}, Sacrifice a Goblin: Tar Pitcher deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "Auntie Grub had caught a goat, a bleating doe that still squirmed in her arms. At the same time, her warren decided to share with her a sensory greeting of hot tar . . . ."\n—A tale of Auntie Grub

name: Boggart Shenanigans
text: Whenever another Goblin you control is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, you may have Boggart Shenanigans deal 1 damage to target player.
flavor: Boggarts revel in discovering new sensations, from the texture of an otter pellet to the squeak of a dying warren mate.

name: Spitting Earth
text: Spitting Earth deals damage to target creature equal to the number of Mountains you control.
flavor: "Within each of you is the strength of a landslide."\n—Kumano, to his pupils

name: Tarfire
text: Tarfire deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "After Auntie brushed the soot from her eyes, she discovered something wonderful: the fire had turned the goat into something that smelled delicious."\n—A tale of Auntie Grub

name: Forgotten Cave
text: Forgotten Cave enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {R} to your mana pool.\nCycling {R} ({R}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Goblin Burrows
text: {T}: Add {C} to your mana pool.\n{1}{R}, {T}: Target Goblin creature gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
